node.text: Classic American Modern with this waterfront rambler located in St. Michaels, Maryland. Built in 1958 (could not find info on the architect) the home had fallen into a desperate state of disrepair but was renovated and restored by the firm of Wiedemann Architects, with interiors by Shaun Jackson. Photos: Anice Hoachlander #mcmdaily #mcmrambler #mcmranchhouse #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com

node.text: A revisit to a classic with the iconic Kaufmann Desert House designed by architect Richard Neutra in 1946. Commissioned by Edgar J. Kaufmann Sr. as a winter getaway (ten years earlier Kaufmann commissioned Frank Lloyd Wright to design Fallingwater) but by the 1980’s the home had suffered from poorly considered reno’s and additions. Listed as a possible tear down when it was put up for sale in 1992 the new owners hired the firm of @marmolradziner and the house was painstakingly restored. Photos: Tim Street-Porter @timstreetporter / Brent Harris / Julius Shulman #mcmdaily #richardneutra #kaufmanndeserthouse #desertmodernism #architecturalicon #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com

node.text: The Studebaker Avanti designed by  Tom Kellogg, Bob Andrews, and John Ebstein of Raymond Loewy’s design firm. Introduced at the 1962 New York International Auto Show the Avanti was conceived as a halo car to help bolster Studebaker‘a lagging sales. But despite favorable reviews the Avanti did not find a market and just under 6000 were sold during its one year production run. Photos: Mecum.com #mcmdaily #tomkellogg #bobandrews #johnebstein #raymondloewy #studebaker #studebakeravanti #classiccars #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com
